content:
My new segment #insomnihacks started today!

First Episode: Extra Lean Eggplant Lasagna. It's #lowcalorie #lowfat #glutenfree and most importantly delicious!

Here's the full recipe + time saving tips:

INGREDIENTS:
1/2 Cup Part Skim Mozzarella
1 small eggplant (roughly 1 lb)
1 lb of 96% percent lean ground beef
1 bell pepper
1 onion
1 tablespoon olive oil
8 oz fat free cottage cheese
3 cups of tomato sauce (natural ingredients, no added sugar)
Salt and pepper to taste

DIRECTIONS:
1.) Chop onion and pepper into roughly half inch pieces or finer
2.) Add olive oil and onions to a pan on medium heat, stir occasionally
3.) Slice the eggplant while the onions cook (don't forget to check on the onions!)
4.) Once onions are soft add the peppers and meat, break meat into crumbles
5.) Once meat browns add two cups of sauce, and salt and pepper to taste. Allow to simmer for at least 5 min 
6.) While sauce simmers: Finish slicing eggplant if needed, get your baking pan(s) out, and clean anything you're not still using
7.) Cover the bottom of your baking pan with a layer of eggplant, followed by a layer of 1/2 the cottage cheese, and 1/2 the meat mixture. Repeat for second layer.
8.) Top with one more layer of eggplant, 1 cup of sauce, and mozzarella cheese
9.) Bake at 350 for 30 minutes (Broil for another 1-2 minutes if you want the top browned)
 
TIPS:
1.) Peel the eggplant for easier slicing, especially if using a mandolin
2.) Chop onions and peppers in bulk and freeze into ice cubes. Next time you need them for a cooked recipe just thaw in the microwave and add to the pan.
3.) If you don't like the texture of cottage cheese try throwing it in the blender or food processor first
4.) For small groups or personal meals divide the ingredients into several smaller lasagnas. You can freeze the leftovers and next time you want some all you'll need to do is reheat.
5.) If using small trays bake in the toaster oven rather than the oven to save money, energy and preheat time.
6.) Use a glass baking dish with lid, this way it can go in the oven, freezer, microwave and dishwasher.
7.) If you're really craving pasta just sub in oven ready lasagna noodles for the eggplant. That'll add about 50 calories per slice which still leaves the total well under 300 calories.
